Championship Playoff

First Playoff [Dec 10, Estadio Centenario; attendance: 55,000]
Nacional             0-0 Peñarol               [after two extra times (60')]
  [Nacional: Aníbal Paz; Raúl Pini, Secundino Arrascaeta; General Viana, Rodolfo Pini,
     Schubert Gambetta; Luis Ernesto Castro, Aníbal Ciocca, Atilio García, Roberto Porta,
     Bibiano Zapirain. Coach: Héctor Castro.
   Peñarol: Roque Gastón Máspoli; Agustín Prado, Sixto Possamai; José Pedro Colturi, Obdulio
     Varela, Luis Prais; José María Ortiz, Domingo Gelpi, Elmo Bovio, Lorenzo Pino, Ernesto
     Vidal. Coach: Aníbal Tejada]
  [Referees: Manuel Domínguez, A. Mancebo, C. Martín]

Second Playoff [Dec 17, Estadio Centenario; attendance: 45,000]
Peñarol              3-2 Nacional
  [Luis Prais 37, Obdulio Varela 59pen, Ernesto Vidal 68; Atilio García 25, 28]
  [Peñarol: Roque Gastón Máspoli; Agustín Prado, Gerardo Spósito; José Pedro Colturi, Obdulio
     Varela, Luis Prais; José María Ortiz, Domingo Gelpi, Elmo Bovio, Lorenzo Pino, Ernesto
     Vidal. Coach: Aníbal Tejada.
   Nacional: Aníbal Paz; Raúl Pini, Secundino Arrascaeta; General Viana, Rodolfo Pini,
     Schubert Gambetta; Juan Alberto Bugallo, Aníbal Ciocca, Atilio García, Roberto Porta,
     Bibiano Zapirain. Coach: Héctor Castro]
  [Referees: Genaro Cirilo, J. Benítez, Tecitore]

Peñarol Champions of Uruguay 1944.

Promoted: Rampla Juniors FC.

Topscorer:

21 - Atilio García (C Nacional dF)



